 "date": "1930-10-07", "dates": ["1930-10-07"], "description": ["NEW BRITAIN DAILY HERALD TUESDAY OCTOBER 7 1930 5 ONLY 9 CONFINED ON DEVILS ISLE Three Aviators Among Lifers at French Penal Colony Douthits Homer Starts Card Barrage WEDNESDAY always BARGAIN DAY Washington D C Oct 7 How Devils Island famous penal station in French Guiana looks from the air is told in a report to the Nj tional Geographic Society by Fred erick Simpich recently in charge of the societys aerial survey party which made a study of air traffic lanes between Washington and Buenos Aires With M Siadous Governor Gen eral of French Guiana writes Mr HimpicK we flew from Cayenne lo devils Island Here Captain Drey fus lanjjuished through long lonely years till freed by Emile Zolas aid His dramatic trial uncovering the amazing Count Esterhazy plot stirred the civilized world Three tiny green dots rise from the sea 21 miles south of Cayenne They form the penal group Isles du Salut which include St Joseph rwith its prison hospital Isle Royale with tiers of tiny stone cells for incorrigibles and Devils is land so famed in tales of fact and fiction Men without women gazed up from behind high walls as we idled overhead For women"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-01T13:37:10.348Z", "group": ["ndnp/ct", "connecticut-state-library-hartford-ct-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn82014519/1930-10-07/ed-1/?sp=5", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930100701:0650/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=399&w=301", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:ct:batch_ct_inxs_ver01:data:sn82014519:00414183566:1930100701:0650/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=799&w=602", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_inxs_ver01/data/sn82014519/00414183566/1930100701/0650.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "loca